            "title": "Laboratory Report"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>All hematological parameters are within normal limits except for mildly elevated hemoglobin and markedly increased platelet distribution width. The elevated hemoglobin may be due to dehydration or other non-pathological causes; clinical correlation is advised. The high platelet distribution width suggests increased platelet size variability, which can be seen in reactive states but is nonspecific. No acute hematological abnormality detected.</td></tr></table></div>"
